# LOGO! PG session capture — real hardware
# device: identNo=45 mode=42 passwordExists=1 leaksCleartext=0 blockReadsWork=0
# source: 0BA6.ES10, WebUSB / CH340, fw V1.07.07, 2026-07-16
#
# Format: one exchange per line, "→ <request hex>   ← <response hex | (nothing)>   (note)".
# The consistency test (test/session-replay.test.ts) replays each request against a FakeDevice
# built from the `# device:` header and asserts the fake produces exactly the recorded response.
# Per-byte region reads (Read Byte loops in readRegion) are logged only as progress summaries by
# the tool, so they are not individual exchanges here.

# --- connect ---
→ 22   ← 06   (Restart — clears the error state)
→ 21   ← 06 03 21 45   (IdentNo 0x45 = 0BA6.ES10)

# --- put in STOP (device was already stopped) ---
→ 55 12 12 aa   ← (nothing)   (STOP command not acknowledged on an already-stopped device)
→ 55 17 17 aa   ← 06 42   (mode = STOP)
→ 02 00 ff 48 ff   ← 06 03 00 ff 48 ff 40   (password IS set)

# --- unlock attempt (step 3) ---
→ 22   ← 06
→ 21   ← 06 03 21 45
→ 55 17 17 aa   ← 06 42
→ 02 00 ff 48 ff   ← 06 03 00 ff 48 ff 40
→ 02 00 ff 1f 00   ← 06 03 00 ff 1f 00 04   (magic 1)
→ 02 00 ff 1f 01   ← 06 03 00 ff 1f 01 00   (magic 2)
→ 01 00 ff 47 40 00   ← 06   (Write Byte 0x00FF4740 = 0x00 — lower protection to level 1)

# --- re-negotiate after the write ---
→ 22   ← 06
→ 21   ← 06 03 21 45
→ 55 17 17 aa   ← 06 42
# (password area 0x0566 ×10 and program probe 0x0EE8 ×16 read all-zero — reads suppressed)

# --- read & decode (step 4) ---
→ 22   ← 06
→ 21   ← 06 03 21 45
→ 55 17 17 aa   ← 06 42
→ 02 00 ff 48 ff   ← 06 03 00 ff 48 ff 40
# (pointer table / wiring / program read byte-wise, all-zero — reads suppressed)
